    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-04-09T09:17:43+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-09T09:17:43+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T23:47:43Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-08T23:47:43Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A cold front sweeps across southern SA today. This front will push the inland trough into the far north, exiting the state early Friday. A cooler southwest to southerly flow will gradually moderate in the wake of the front as a strong high pressure system moves in from the west from Friday, establishing in the Bight on Sunday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW009" description="Flinders" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-04-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. High chance of showers south of Hawker, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm in the late morning and afternoon. Winds northwesterly 30 to 45 km/h turning west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h during the afternoon and evening. Daytime maximum temperatures 25 to 32.</text>
                <text type="fire_danger">Moderate</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 9:30am to 3:10pm, UV Index predicted to reach 7 [High]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-04-10T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-09T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower near the coast, most likely in the early morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 11 and 15 with daytime temperatures reaching between 17 and 23.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-04-11T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-10T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Medium chance of showers south of Hawker, most likely in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds southwesterly 20 to 30 km/h turning southerly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 8 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 14 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-04-12T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-04-13T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-04-11T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-04-12T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower near the coast, most likely in the morning. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds south to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h tending south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 6 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 20.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
